    {
      "block_id": "p1_b13",
      "text": "Rotator cuff tears are the most common upper extremity condition seen ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        251.24562072753906,
        429.6253662109375,
        266.0536193847656
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1046,
        1790,
        1108
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b14",
      "text": "by primary care and orthopaedic surgeons, with a spectrum ranging ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        267.2416076660156,
        408.4679260253906,
        282.0495910644531
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1113,
        1701,
        1175
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b15",
      "text": "from tendinopathy to full-thickness tears with arthritic change. Some ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        283.23760986328125,
        416.0267028808594,
        298.04559326171875
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1180,
        1733,
        1241
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b16",
      "text": "tears are traumatic, but most rotator cuff problems are degenerative. ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        299.2336120605469,
        413.82958984375,
        314.0415954589844
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1246,
        1724,
        1308
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b17",
      "text": "Not all tears are symptomatic and not all progress, and many patients ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        315.2296142578125,
        413.98919677734375,
        330.03759765625
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1313,
        1724,
        1375
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b18",
      "text": "in whom tears become more extensive do not experience symptom ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        331.2256164550781,
        403.32122802734375,
        346.0335998535156
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1380,
        1680,
        1441
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b19",
      "text": "worsening. Hence, a standard algorithm for managing patients is ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        347.22161865234375,
        390.7031555175781,
        362.02960205078125
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1446,
        1627,
        1508
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b20",
      "text": "challenging. The pathophysiology of rotator cuff tears is complex ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        363.2176208496094,
        395.13836669921875,
        378.0256042480469
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1513,
        1646,
        1575
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b21",
      "text": "and encompasses an interplay between the tendon, bone and muscle. ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        379.213623046875,
        415.4327392578125,
        394.0216064453125
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1580,
        1730,
        1641
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b22",
      "text": "Rotator cuff tears begin as degenerative changes within the tendon, ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        395.2096252441406,
        405.4739685058594,
        410.0176086425781
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1646,
        1689,
        1708
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b23",
      "text": "with matrix disorganization and inflammatory changes. Subsequently, ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        411.20562744140625,
        422.7575988769531,
        426.01361083984375
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1713,
        1761,
        1775
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b24",
      "text": "tears progress to partial-thickness and then full-thickness tears. Muscle ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        427.2016296386719,
        426.3396301269531,
        442.0096130371094
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1780,
        1776,
        1841
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b25",
      "text": "quality, as evidenced by the overall size of the muscle and intramuscular ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        443.1976318359375,
        429.0168151855469,
        458.005615234375
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1846,
        1787,
        1908
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b26",
      "text": "fatty infiltration, also influences symptoms, tear progression and the ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        459.1936340332031,
        411.9708251953125,
        474.0016174316406
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1913,
        1716,
        1975
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b27",
      "text": "outcomes of surgery. Treatment depends primarily on symptoms, with ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        475.18963623046875,
        423.94793701171875,
        489.99761962890625
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        1979,
        1766,
        2041
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b28",
      "text": "non-operative management sufficient for most patients with rotator ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        491.1856384277344,
        409.5,
        505.9936218261719
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        2046,
        1706,
        2108
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b29",
      "text": "cuff problems. Modern arthroscopic repair techniques have improved ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        507.1816711425781,
        419.862060546875,
        521.9896850585938
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        2113,
        1749,
        2174
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b30",
      "text": "recovery, but outcomes are still limited by a lack of understanding of ",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        523.1776123046875,
        410.2788391113281,
        537.9856567382812
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
        165,
        2179,
        1709,
        2241
      ],
      "column_guess": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p1_b31",
      "text": "how to improve tendon to bone healing in many patients.",
      "bbox_pt": [
        39.68510055541992,
        539.173583984375,
        346.93316650390625,
        553.9816284179688
      ],
      "bbox_px": [
